fields.label: Select your role in the organization

confirmations.name: Default Confirmation
confirmations.message: Thank you for creating a DOCC app account and for your interest in the ACGME’s Direct Observation of Clinical Care app. The DOCC app is being made available to individuals, programs and institutions as a downloadable tool that can be adapted for local use at no charge. This temporary account allows you to use the DOCC app and test its utility in helping you assess resident/fellow competencies in a variety of clinical settings. If after testing you decide that you would like to install the DOCC app locally, please contact the ACGME’s Office of Distance Learning at de@acgme.org; the Office will send you a .zip file with the app files and instructions on how to install them on a local computer. Programs and institutions have the option of housing the files on a local server, integrating the app with a residency management system or arranging the app to be hosted by an online hosting service. For assistance with local installation, please contact support@design.garden. Arranging a hosting service for the DOCC app is the responsibility of the program and/or institution. The ACGME will not pay for a local program’s/institution’s hosting fee. Your access to your DOCC app account as a trial user will be supported for one year (365 days), after which it will be removed. Please contact the Office of Distance Learning at de@acgme.org with any questions. Continue to login
